# Desktop sidecar OPTIONAL MLX local-STT add-on (v0.4.4 S12a, docs/
# design-explorations/s12-mlx-blueprint.md §C R1) — parakeet-mlx, the
# Apple-Silicon-only backend behind the parakeet-tdt-0.6b-v3 model.
# UNLIKE requirements-diar.txt (installed on TOP of the shared base
# venv), this rides a SEPARATE, hash-locked venv (`<app-data>/mlx-
# venv`, Rust `venv_for_model(model)` picks it for `parakeet-*`) — §B
# finding 8 found the shared-venv plan unsatisfiable: parakeet-mlx's
# own transitive tree pulls librosa -> numba, and numba 0.66.0 declares
# `numpy<2.5,>=1.22`, which cannot coexist with the base venv's pinned
# `numpy==2.5.1` (requirements-sidecar.txt) in one environment. A
# separate venv sidesteps the conflict entirely rather than trying to
# resolve it — faster-whisper and parakeet-mlx never share an
# environment, so the numba/numpy clash is structurally impossible.
#
# This file is the uv pip compile SOURCE — commit requirements-mlx.lock
# (generated from this file, hash-pinned) as the actual bundled Tauri
# resource; this .in file itself is not installed from directly.
# Regenerate the lock with EXACTLY (§C R1, flags verified against the
# pinned uv 0.11.28's own `uv pip compile --help`; the exact command is
# also self-recorded in requirements-mlx.lock's own header via
# --custom-compile-command, so it never drifts from what actually
# produced the committed file):
#   MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=14.0 uv pip compile requirements-mlx.in \
#     -o requirements-mlx.lock --python-platform aarch64-apple-darwin \
#     --python-version 3.12 --generate-hashes --upgrade
#
# TWO non-obvious footguns discovered live generating this file
# (2026-07-16), both silent — neither errors, both just quietly pick an
# older/wrong package:
#   1. MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET is REQUIRED. Without it, uv's generic
#      `aarch64-apple-darwin` platform target defaults to a macOS 13
#      floor and silently resolves mlx down to 0.29.3 (the newest
#      version still shipping a macosx_13_0_arm64 wheel — mlx 0.30.0+
#      dropped macOS 13 entirely, macosx_14_0_arm64+ only). This
#      project's actual gate is macOS >=14.0 (docs/design-explorations/
#      s12-mlx-blueprint.md §C Gating/F13 — mlx_capabilities() requires
#      native arm64 + macOS >=14.0), so resolving against a macOS 13
#      floor is both needlessly conservative AND drifts from the
#      blueprint's own verified-live evidence (mlx 0.32.0, §9). Setting
#      MACOSX_DEPLOYMENT_TARGET=14.0 resolves mlx/mlx-metal to 0.32.0
#      instead — verified this is the ONLY package the flag moves (a
#      full package-list diff against the macOS-13-floor resolution
#      showed zero other version changes).
#   2. --upgrade is REQUIRED on every regeneration. `uv pip compile`
#      treats an EXISTING file at -o as a preference/pin source (like
#      pip-compile's own incremental behavior) UNLESS --upgrade is
#      passed — re-running the command with an already-present (even
#      stale/wrong, e.g. the macOS-13-floor mlx==0.29.3 above)
#      requirements-mlx.lock already on disk silently keeps reusing its
#      old pins instead of re-resolving fresh, even across an unrelated
#      env-var change. --no-cache alone does NOT fix this (verified
#      live: still returned 0.29.3); only --upgrade (or deleting the
#      file first) does.
#
# NEVER installed into any dev/CI venv to generate this lock — `uv pip
# compile` only resolves, it doesn't install (verified: this repo's own
# sidecar/.venv has neither parakeet-mlx nor mlx present after
# generating requirements-mlx.lock).
#
# websockets pinned to match the base venv's own exact pin
# (requirements-sidecar.txt: websockets==13.1) — whisper_server.py's
# module-level `import websockets` must resolve identically whichever
# venv (base or mlx) actually runs it (§C R1: "every module-level
# import of whisper_server.py must be satisfiable in the mlx venv...
# one file runs under either venv"); parakeet-mlx itself doesn't
# depend on websockets at all, so this entry exists purely for that
# shared-file-two-venvs invariant, not a parakeet-mlx transitive need.
#
# parakeet-mlx==0.5.2 (Apache-2.0, verified live against PyPI's JSON
# API 2026-07-16): requires_dist = dacite>=1.9.2, huggingface-hub>=
# 0.30.2, librosa>=0.11.0, mlx>=0.22.1, numpy>=2.2.5, typer>=0.15.3;
# requires_python>=3.10; torch-free. See requirements-mlx.lock's own
# resolved tree + this repo's S12a A4 worker report for the full
# transitive dependency/license inventory (soxr LGPL-2.1-or-later via
# librosa, libsndfile LGPL-2.1-or-later via soundfile — both flagged
# for the release NOTICE).
parakeet-mlx==0.5.2
websockets==13.1
